data.value:
What does this software do? This software sends every second a network-ping ( https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ping_(networking_utility) ) to servers in the United Kingdom, Germany, US-East, US-West, and Australia and displays in it's overlay-window the latency and the jitter as well as a graphical visualization of the latency. Utilizing this tool, network-lags and the usage of so-called "lag-switches" will become easier to detect.
The 3 columns of the overlay: 1. Global location 2. Ping response time 3. Network jitter
This project is open-source: https://github.com/EmanueleCiriachi/Honest-Fighter-Initiative
The idea is that as many pilots as possible join this initiative and use this overlay during the fight so that it can be seen in their videos. If many do this, there will be enormous pressure on the pilots who do not use it.
Feel free to join the official Discord-server of the Honest Fighter Initiative: https://discord.gg/zYqTBXR2nh
We also offer specially protected versions for e-sports organizers. For interested parties please contact "Akuma Tebori#0001" on Discord.
